value.name: Sagelva vasskraftsenter
value.snippet: Sagelva vasskraftsenter - med vatn som drivkraft i 300 år. Hos oss kan dere oppleve 300 års bruk av vasskraft på Stueflotten øverst i Romsdalen. Ildsjeler har bygget opp og driver Sagelva vasskraftsenter. Gjennom sommeren viser vi fram og demonstrerer et fullskala anlegg drevet av vatn.

value.name: Sagelva Hydropower Center - From waterfall to hydropower
value.snippet: Sagelva Hydropower Center in the Romsdalen valley near Bjorli, is built on the remains of the old local sawmill. Where the rivers Asbjørnsåa and Ulvåa meet, this is the perfect place to demonstrate in full scale the history of water power exploration in the region.

value.name: Stella power stations - Wikipedia
value.snippet: The power stations were built in the "brick cathedral" design style. The main visible features of the stations were their large boiler houses, turbine halls, cooling towers and pairs of chimneys; other facilities on both sites included offices, coal sorting areas, small fire stations and workshops.
